- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses a neural network-based approach for the task. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the automated detection of emotions in text. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses a neural network-based approach. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with information retrieval, but it does involve the use of pre-trained word embeddings to incorporate contextual knowledge about words into the model.
